source_jobs.description:
We are looking for a Senior Engineer to join our Payments & Wallet team (also known as PAW 🐾) — the core group handling asset management, compliance, and On-chain Services & Integrations (Superwallet) at Coinhako.

In this role, you will be responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining high-performance services that power our payments and wallet infrastructure. You’ll collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure seamless integration across systems, optimize transaction workflows, and enhance platform reliability and scalability.



What you'll be doing:

 - Architect and build scalable backend services. Our tech stack is Rails 7, Go, Sidekiq, REST, AWS, Docker;

 - Design and build high-volume APIs used by our frontends and external traders;

 - Take initiative to ensure the long-term quality of the code and drive decisions related to the architecture of production systems;

 - Manage and maintain custody solutions for digital assets. Ensure the highest level of security and compliance in handling and storing digital assets, including cryptocurrencies, tokens, and digital records;

 - Collaborate with other engineers, product managers and designers during various product development stages;

 - Improve engineering standards, tooling, and processes.



What we're looking for:

 - Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field;

 - Understand good practices of building and working with APIs;

 - Have 5+ years of building scalable distributed systems with a strong background in Ruby, Go is a plus;

 - Comfortable with ambiguity and scoping solutions with your teammates;

 - You’re organized, proactive and can be your own manager;

 - Knowledge of cryptography and security principles in blockchain as well as compliance and regulatory frameworks for cryptocurrency.



What’s in it for you:

 - Friendly and fun start-up work culture

 - Convenient work location located in the heart of CBD area

 - Generous annual leaves on top of national holidays

 - Medical coverage including GP, Specialist, TCM, and more

 - Self-care benefits and exciting fitness workshops/webinars

 - Vibrant office with a well-stocked pantry



Find out more about Coinhako @https://www.coinhako.com/ and don't forget to visit our Careers Page @https://www.coinhako.com/join-us!



By submitting your application to us, you consent to the collection, use, disclosure and processing of your personal data in accordance with our privacy policy, which is accessible at https://www.coinhako.com/legal/sg-1/privacy_policy.
